## Implementation Considerations

### Performance

- Optimize Git repositories to handle large microservices codebases efficiently.
- Use shallow clones or sparse checkouts for performance in large repositories.

### Security

- Implement secure access controls for Git repositories to protect sensitive microservices code.
- Use signed commits to ensure code integrity.

### Scalability

- Design Git workflows to scale with growing microservices architectures.
- Leverage Git's branching model to manage multiple microservices simultaneously.

